"Ihm B.-S., Lee J.-S., Kim J.-W., Kim J.-H.","Relationship between global warming and species richness of vascular plants",2007,"Journal of Plant Biology","50","3",,"321","324",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34547730751&partnerID=40&md5=7b1bdf17790a7764eed35b6f945f2fed","Department of Biology, Mokpo National University, Muan 534-729, South Korea; Department of Biology, Kunsan National University, Kunsan 573-701, South Korea; Department of Biological Science, Seoul National University, Seoul 151-742, South Korea","Ihm, B.-S., Department of Biology, Mokpo National University, Muan 534-729, South Korea; Lee, J.-S., Department of Biology, Kunsan National University, Kunsan 573-701, South Korea; Kim, J.-W., Department of Biology, Mokpo National University, Muan 534-729, South Korea; Kim, J.-H., Department of Biological Science, Seoul National University, Seoul 151-742, South Korea","We analyzed climatological and geographical variables in 90 countries from the Northern Hemisphere to determine the significant variability of plant species richness as it relates to broad-scale levels of global warming. This variability was quantified by the parameters of temperature and precipitation. Of the 27 temperature variables and 13 precipitation variables, 6 variables had negative influences on species richness while 5 variables had positive impacts. When we estimated the effect of higher temperatures, we found that a 1 or 2°C rise in global warming produced an increase in species richness of 1.6 or 3.2%, respectively.","Global warming; Maximum temperature; Minimum temperature; Precipitation; Species richness increase","Tracheophyta",,,,,,"Adams, J.M., Woodward, E.I., Patterns in tree species richness as a test of the glacial extinction hypothesis (1989) Nature, 339, pp. 699-701; Alward, R.D., Detling, J.K., Milchunas, D.G., Grassland vegetation changes and nocturnal global warming (1999) Science, 283, pp. 229-231; Bao, Y., Zhou, H.F., Hong, D.Y., Ge, S., Gen